{
  "texts": [
    "However, four problems arise, some more significant than others, requiring new ideas that need to be implemented in the entire procedure.",
    "As these adjustments cannot really be separated from the rest of the argument, we provide in Section 5 a complete detailed proof, even if it has large overlaps with the aforementioned works.",
    "Here we make the best attempt to point out the changes made to the argument, without getting into too many details.",
    "Our goal is to construct some ρ having the prescribed properties together with a weak * open neighbourhood U.",
    "The changes done to the construction of ρ from [11] and [22] can broadly be characterised as (i) considering Lipschitz maps as opposed to biLipschitz, (ii) considering possibly infinite sums of Jacobians, (iii) allowing the Jacobians det Dπ i to be multiplied with the coefficients f i (which are Lipschitz functions), (iv) finding an entire weak * open set of right hand sides ρ as opposed to a single one.The first and the second item are the most complicated to deal with."
  ]
}